node.text: These old-fashioned apples have lovely names like ‘Firecracracker’ and ‘Flower of Kent’ and flesh tinged with color. Let’s see what they taste like!

node.text: My easy pickled peppers. 🌶🌶🌶I put these on everything, scrambled eggs, sandwiches, noodles…anytime I’m looking for a smack of tangy garlic heat. 🔥

node.text: Dear Minnesota, I made my first hot dish. Tiling tater tots is totally fun.  Love, Emmy

node.text: 💕5 million of you on Facebook find me and my experiments worthy of a follow. THANK YOU! Thank you for tuning-in, sticking around, and supporting my curiosity. I’m grateful to you all. THANK YOU! 💕

node.text: I made this for those that find themselves struck by a moment of indecision. More details coming soon…in the meanwhile, please share your feelings about this edible chimera. 🍔➕🌭

node.text: ✨Magnificent home grown glass gem corn. 🌈 Thank you @bakercreekseeds for offering such magical seeds. #nofilter

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Emmy on September 02, 2021 tagging @bakercreekseeds. May be an image of corn.

node.text: I grew corn for the first time this year. 👏🏼This heirloom variety from @bakercreekseeds is called strawberry popcorn and I cannot wait to pop it! 🍿

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Emmy on September 01, 2021. May be an image of fruit and indoor.

node.text: Oh, captured; the ignorance of the unleashed liquid carnage to come. 🤢 Find all the gory details in my Stories.
